"&#xa0;\nBNI0013Written evidence submitted by The Post Office Limited&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n1.1 \nWe are pleased to submit evidence to the Northern Ireland Affairs Committee’s inquiry into the banking structure in Northern Ireland. \n&#xa0;\n1.2 \nThis submission will cover the key facts about The Post Office, our relationships with the Bank of Ireland,\n First Tr\nust Bank,\n Ulster Bank and \nDanske\n Bank, and our role in the provision of a full product range of financial services.\n&#xa0;&#xa0;\n2.1 \nThe Post Office is one of the UK’s fastest growing financial service providers in the UK. We have:\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n2.2 \nAt \nThe\n Post Office we offer a range of financial s\nervices products to meet the needs of all customers including products that promote financial inclusion\n.\n&#xa0;\n2.3 \nWe have a nationwide network that provides access to customers including those in remotest areas and areas of deprivation. Our network enables all\n customers to have convenient access to cash.\n&#xa0;\n2.4 \nOur approach to our own financial services products is to ensure that they are simple, fa\nir, \ntransparent\n and value for money, supported by widest access\n.\n&#xa0;\n2.5 \nAside from our own products, we can also \nprovide\n over the counter access for cash withdrawals to \n95 per cent of \ncurrent account \ndebit card holders and it remains our aspiration for all \nbanks to offer their customers access via Post Office branches. \n&#xa0;\n2.6 \nThe Post Office is going from strength to \nstrength in the mortgage market and this has become more evident over the last few years as we continue to offer some of the most competitive rates direct to consumers.\n \nWe are committed to being fully transparent with our customers and in return, they kno\nw they will receive excellent service from a brand they can trust.\n We are also recognised as being the leading provider of foreign exchange products in the UK market.\n&#xa0;\n2.7 \nAt \nThe\n Post Office we continue to develop a full range of financial service products\n and we recently launched a trial of \nour current accounts in East Anglia.\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n3.1 \nIn the context of Northern Ireland \nthe\n Post Office has 484 branches and of these \naround \n33\n0 or 68\n per cent are \nin \nrural\n locations. \nThere are 28 Post Office/Ba\nnk of Ireland ATMs in Northern Ireland and some branches will have ATMs provided by other suppliers. \n&#xa0;\n3.2 \nWe are committed to maintaining a nationwide network of Post Office branches and we continue to meet the access criteria stipulated by the Government\n. \n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n4.1 \nMany of The Post Office’s financial service products are provided in partnership with the Bank of Ireland and the two companies have built a successful partnership over the past decade\n. \nTogether we provide a comprehensive range of \nproducts to 3 million customers and we have a savings book valued at £17 billion.\n&#xa0;\n4.2 \nThe Bank of Ireland’s UK business was incorporated into a separate ring-fenced UK company on 1 November 2010 which means that depositors are protected under the \nFinancia\nl Services Compensation Scheme (FSCS).\n&#xa0;\n4.3 \nBank of Ireland \npersonal, business and basic bank account \ncustomers can access cash withdrawal\ns\n, balance enquir\nies,\n cash and cheque deposit services at Post Office counters.\n We also provide BOI business customers\n with a change giving service in nominated branches.\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;5.1 \nAs with the majority of high street banks, The Post Office has a relationship with Ulster Bank whereby their \npersonal and basic account \ncustomers can access cash withdrawal and balance \nenquiry services at Post Office counters\n. \n&#xa0;&#xa0;6.1 \nThe Post Office has a long standing relationship with First Trust \nwhich \nallows their 3\n,000\n basic bank account customers to access cash withdrawals and balance enquiries.\n \nWe are currently working\n with First Trust to expand access to these products to around 100\n,000\n \nof their \npersonal \naccount debit card holders\n in the months ahead. \n&#xa0;&#xa0;\n7.1 \nThe Post Office also has a relationship with \nDanske\n Bank whereby their \npersonal\n, business\n and basic \naccount customers\n can \naccess cash withdrawal and balance enquiry services at Post Office counters so long as they have the appropriate card and pin number. Customers can also make a cash deposit, and in Northern Ireland only a cheque deposit service is ava\nilable. \n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n8.1 \nThe Post Office also provides access to banking services for other banks and building societies:\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nSeptember 2013\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n"